[[File:Adrianov compass.gif|thumb|right|320px|Adrianov compass in details: 1) Compass case; 2) Scale; 3)&nbsp;Magnetic&nbsp; pointer; 4) Sight point; 5) Counter point; 6)&nbsp;Pointer&nbsp;stopper]] The '''Adrianov compass''' ({{lang-ru|Компас Адрианова}}) is a military [[compass]] designed by [[Imperial Russian Army|Russian Imperial Army]] [[topography|topographist]] Vladimir Adrianov in 1907. Wrist-worn versions of the compass were then adopted and widely used by the [[Red Army|Red]] and [[Soviet Army]].<ref name="popov" >{{cite book |last1= Popov|first1= A. M. |title= Начальная военная подготовка (учебник) |trans-title=Basic military training course (a handbook) |year= 1978 |publisher= [[DOSAAF]] |location= Moscow |language= Russian |isbn= |oclc= 316895320 |page= 219 |postscript= Available at [[Pennsylvania State University Libraries|Pennsylvania State University Library]] }}</ref>
