[[File:Lobster forks.jpg|thumb|200px|Three lobster forks]]A '''lobster pick''' or '''lobster fork''' is a long, narrow [[food utensil]] used to extract meat from joints, legs, claws, and other small parts of a [[lobster]].  Lobster picks are usually made of [[stainless steel]] and weigh as much as an average [[teaspoon]]. They have a long, textured cylindrical handle, ending in a crescent-shaped moderately sharp pick, or else a small two-tined [[fork]]. The other end may have a [[spoon]] for scooping out meat from inside the lobster.<ref name="tips">[http://www.recipetips.com/glossary-term/t--37385/lobster-pick.asp Lobster Pick.] Recipetips.com. Retrieved 17 April 2011.</ref> The lobster pick can also be used with other [[seafood]], such as [[crab]] and [[crawfish]].<ref name="tips" />

